      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) that exemplifies mechanical excellence. The S54 3.2L power plant has been meticulously maintained, featuring a documented VANOS bulletproofing and preventative rod bearing replacement with high-performance treated shells. Power is managed via a crisp 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-differential lock, both operating at factory tolerances. The chassis is structurally impeccable, having received proactive subframe reinforcement to ensure long-term torsional rigidity. The suspension retains its original geometry with refreshed OEM bushings for precise turn-in response. Clad in its original factory finish with no signs of oxidation or clear coat failure, this M3 is a turn-key specimen for the purist who demands both aesthetic perfection and peak mechanical performance.",
